 ('480', '31', '6', '1', 'en_us', '16', '', '{\"typeId\":\"6\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gregg Stokes\",\"slug\":\"gregg-stokes\",\"postDate\":1408726800,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"16\":\"<p>Gregg has more than 20 years experience in the world of corporate communications and has led creative teams from a variety of positions, including Art Director, Creative Director and Producer.<\\/p><p>Known throughout the industry for the stunning visuals he creates in all mediums, Gregg is a strong conceptual and creative thinker who focuses on finding practical and innovative solutions to any creative challenge. Whether it\\u2019s print, video, animation, or motion graphics, Gregg\\u2019s visual thinking helps transform complex or mundane messages into easy-to-understand, visually compelling iconography.<\\/p><p>Gregg\\u2019s professional career began as a sought-after pen and ink illustrator while still pursuing his BA at the University of Nevada, Reno. After graduating with a degree in Theatre, he embarked on a creative journey that continues to this day and has included jobs as a professional dancer, actor and singer, as well as managing art departments and leading staffs of art directors, writers and designers.<\\/p><p>As Art Director and Creative Director for Encore Productions from 1993 \\u2013 2002, Gregg was responsible for the overall look and feel of the company\\u2019s creative work for a broad roster of clients, including Intel, Microsoft, Redken 5th Avenue, IBM, John Paul Mitchell, Hewlett-Packard, Park Place Entertainment, Toyota, Cadillac, Mannington Floors and many others. His role required him to lead the visual design process from concept through production while managing multiple creative teams.<\\/p><p>For the last fifteen years, Gregg and Clarity founder, Bill Welter have worked as creative partners, designing and producing hundreds of high-profile media and live event projects worldwide for some of the world\\u2019s best known an