 ('537', '31', '6', '1', 'en_us', '26', '', '{\"typeId\":\"6\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gregg Stokes\",\"slug\":\"gregg-stokes\",\"postDate\":1408728600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"16\":\"<p>Gregg has more than 20 years experience in the world of corporate communications and has led creative teams from a variety of positions, including Art Director, Creative Director and Producer.<\\/p><p>As Art & Creative Director for Encore Productions from 1993 \\u2013 2002, Gregg was responsible for the overall look and feel of the company\\u2019s creative work for clients such as Intel, Microsoft, IBM, John Paul Mitchell, Hewlett-Packard, Toyota, Cadillac, and more.  Throughout he led the visual design process from concept through production while managing multiple creative teams.<\\/p><p>For the last fifteen years, Gregg has partnered with Clarity founder, Bill Welter, designing and producing hundreds of high-profile media and live event projects worldwide for some of the world\\u2019s best known and successful companies.  Whether it\\u2019s print, video, animation, or motion graphics, Gregg\\u2019s visual thinking helps transform complex or mundane messages into easy-to-understand, visually compelling iconography.<\\/p>\",\"20\":\"gregg.stokes\",\"11\":[\"199\"],\"19\":\"3geezy\",\"21\":\"pub\\/gregg-stokes\\/1\\/750\\/2b6\",\"12\":\"Partner and Executive Art Director\",\"9\":[\"179\"],\"18\":\"@greggstokes\",\"22\":\"\"}}', '2014-09-30 06:06:10', '2014-09-30 06:06:10', 'eca6fcde-a7cf-4545-83f2-c054bd09b936'),
 ('538', '30', '6', '1', 'en_us', '18', '', '{\"typeId\":\"6\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Bill Welter\",\"slug\":\"bill-welter\",\"postDate\":1408730400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"16\":\"<p>Bill is the founder of Clarity Creative Group and has over 20 years experience in the strategic & creative design and development of corporate communications, presentations and events of all kinds.<\\/p><p>Though he has done work for dozens of Fortune 500 companies, Bill has been engaged primarily with Intel Corporation for the last five years.  During that time, he has worked closely with Intel\\u2019s senior-level executives and their teams to enhance message effectiveness of high-profile internal and external events globally.<\\/p><p>Through their involvement with hundreds of Intel events in nearly 30 countries, Bill and his team have garnered invaluable experience in the best ways to support executive speakers and create compelling, easy-to-customize media.<\\/p><p>He formed Clarity Creative Group with the goal of providing a new brand of world-class communications strategy and creative execution to a small roster of select clients.<\\/p>\",\"20\":\"\",\"11\":[\"182\"],\"19\":\"\",\"21\":\"\",\"12\":\"Founder and Executive Creative Director\",\"9\":[\"142\"],\"18\":\"\",\"22\":\"\"}}', '2014-09-30 06:06:21', '2014-09-30 06:06:21', '7097e172-7469-4e40-b346-0d6939ec7bb3'),
 ('539', '30', '6', '1', 'en_us', '19', '', '{\"typeId\":\"6\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Bill Welter\",\"slug\":\"bill-welter\",\"postDate\":1408730400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"16\":\"<p>Bill is the founder of Clarity Creative Group and has over 20 years experience in the strategic & creative design and development of corporate communications, presentations and events of all kinds.<\\/p><p>Though he has done work for dozens of Fortune 500 companies, Bill has been engaged primarily with the technology industry for the last decade.  During that time, he has worked closely with senior-level executives and their teams to enhance message effectiveness of high-profile internal and external events and campaigns on a global scale.<\\/p><p>Through their involvement with hundreds of events in nearly 30 countries, Bill and his team have garnered invaluable experience in the best ways to support executive speakers and create fresh, engaging media \\u2013 often on nearly impossible timelines.<\\/p><p>He formed Clarity Creative Group in 2002 with the goal of providing a new brand of world-class communications strategy and creative execution to a small roster of select clients.<\\/p>\",\"20\":\"\",\"11\":[\"182\"],\"19\":\"\",\"21\":\"\",\"12\":\"Founder and Executive Creative Director\",\"9\":[\"142\"],\"18\":\"\",\"22\":\"\"}}', '2014-09-30 15:11:55', '2014-09-30 15:11:55', '05683876-3ef9-4c39-b521-abcac77d30f6'),
 ('540', '31', '6', '1', 'en_us', '27', '', '{\"typeId\":\"6\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gregg Stokes\",\"slug\":\"gregg-stokes\",\"postDate\":1408728600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"16\":\"<p>Gregg has more than 20 years experience in the world of corporate communications and has led creative teams from a variety of positions, including Art Director, Creative Director and Producer.<\\/p><p>As Art & Creative Director for Encore Productions from 1993 \\u2013 2002, Gregg was responsible for the overall look and feel of the company\\u2019s creative work for clients such as Intel, Microsoft, IBM, John Paul Mitchell, Hewlett-Packard, Toyota, Cadillac, and more.  Throughout he led the visual design process from concept through production while managing multiple creative teams.<\\/p><p>For more than 15 fifteen years, Gregg has partnered with Clarity founder, Bill Welter, designing and producing hundreds of high-profile media and live event projects worldwide for some of the world\\u2019s best known and successful companies.  Whether it\\u2019s print, video, animation, or motion graphics, Gregg\\u2019s visual thinking helps transform complex or mundane messages into easy-to-understand, visually compelling iconography.<\\/p>\",\"20\":\"gregg.stokes\",\"11\":[\"199\"],\"19\":\"3geezy\",\"21\":\"pub\\/gregg-stokes\\/1\\/750\\/2b6\",\"12\":\"Partner and Executive Art Director\",\"9\":[\"179\"],\"18\":\"@greggstokes\",\"22\":\"\"}}', '2014-09-30 15:14:11', '2014-09-30 15:14:11', '1b9fd272-d5f5-474a-b7f1-a7aaa5515a28'),
 ('541', '32', '6', '1', 'en_us', '16', '', '{\"typeId\":\"6\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Steven Pine\",\"slug\":\"steven-pine\",\"postDate\":1408726800,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"16\":\"<p>Steven Pine<\\/p><p>Steven has worked on every side of the creative process for over 25 years, collaborating for the last 15 years with Bill Welter & Gregg Stokes to communicate some of Intel\\u2019s most memorable stories and stage their biggest events.  Fusing his directing & production skills; ease with actors & executives alike; and his knowledge of the tech industry, he has produced and directed hundreds of videos and live events for Clarity.<\\/p><p>Prior to Clarity, Steven scratched the acting \\u201citch\\u201d in NY and LA, which led to hosting technology trade shows and corporate videos.  He has shared the stage (and camera lens) with some of the tech industry\\u2019s biggest names, including Paul Otellini and Andy Grove of Intel. <\\/p><p>As an editor at CNBC, NBC and MSG Networks, Steven honed his skills in the story-telling business, also working as cameraman for NBC focusing on Katie Couric.  These days, his focus is on defining the fundamental marketing & communications challenges at Clarity Creative.<\\/p>\",\"20\":\"\",\"11\":[\"219\"],\"19\":\"\",\"21\":\"\",\"12\":\"Partner and Executive Producer\",\"9\":[\"181\"],\"18\":\"@Steveninnyc \",\"22\":\"\"}}', '2014-10-01 16:36:37', '2014-10-01 16:36:37', '5d92a9c1-9503-4d4d-ab3f-cfedf52da114'),
 ('542', '38', '4', '1', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Against All Odds - Ali vs. Forman\",\"slug\":\"against-all-odds-ali-vs.-forman\",\"postDate\":1408334100,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"4\":[\"4\",\"10\",\"11\"],\"7\":\"Intel\",\"2\":\"<p>On October 30, 1974, Ali, described by many as \\u201cpast his prime\\u201d and \\u201cover the hill\\u201d took on the odds-on favorite, George Forman at the famous \\u2018Rumble In The Jungle\\u2019 in Zaire, Africa.  Who had the \\u2018Will To Win\\u2019?  This video harnessed the emotions and lessons of one of the most famous fights in history to introduce the theme for a global sales conference:  \\u201cThe Will To Win.\\u201d<\\/p>\",\"13\":\"\",\"14\":\"\",\"10\":\"1\",\"8\":\"The Will to Win\",\"3\":[\"149\",\"152\"],\"6\":\"97147782\",\"23\":\"\",\"5\":\"\",\"17\":\"\"}}', '2014-10-01 18:53:33', '2014-10-01 18:53:33', 'cc084130-b6cf-4853-8031-4bb25219173d'),
